<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="142" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1697,2042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="141">1. Elytra shorter than pronotum, 0.9 times as long as pronotum, sides divergent to posterior margin, widest at posterior margin. ................................................................................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1697,2042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="141">- Elytra longer than pronotum, ranging between 1.1 and 1.4 times as long as pronotum, sides slightly curved, widest in front of posterior margin...................................................................................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1697,2042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="141">2. Eyes reduced, approximately only 0.20 times as long as total length of head; postocular length more the two times longer than eyes; elytra unicolored or not conspicuously bicolored........................................................ 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1697,2042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
- Eyes less reduced, approximately 0.30 times as long as total length of head; postocular length only 1.6 times as long as eyes; elytra conspicuously bicolored, with distinct black anterior half......................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1933" box="[1335,1436,1903,1925]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudastenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barretoi">
<emphasis box="[1335,1436,1903,1925]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">P. barretoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1697,2042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
3. Eyes slightly larger; postocular sides approximately parallel; elytra slightly bicolored, anterior half of elytra indistinctly darker than posterior half.......................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Busanello &amp; Irmler &amp; Caron" authorityYear="2020" box="[1286,1436,1962,1983]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudastenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ribeirocostae">
<emphasis box="[1286,1436,1962,1983]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">P. ribeirocostae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1697,2042]" box="[151,1437,1991,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<keyLead box="[151,1437,1991,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
- Eyes slightly smaller; postocular sides divergent; elytra unicolored yellow................................ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Busanello &amp; Irmler &amp; Caron" authorityYear="2020" box="[1322,1437,1991,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudastenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schubarti">
<emphasis box="[1322,1437,1991,2013]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">P. schubarti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1697,2042]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,153,439]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="142" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<keyStep lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="142" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,2020,2042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
4. Eyes large, 0.33 times as long as total length of head; postocular length equal to eye length................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Busanello &amp; Irmler &amp; Caron" authorityYear="2020" box="[1331,1436,2020,2042]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudastenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculatus">
<emphasis box="[1331,1436,2020,2042]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">P. oculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="142">- Eyes smaller, between 0.24 and 0.31 times as long as total length of head; postocular length distinctly longer than eye length ................................................................................................... 5</keyLead>
</keyStep>
</paragraph>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,439]" box="[151,1436,212,234]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,212,234]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">5. Pronotum light brown; elytra with basal half darker than apical half (in some specimens not so conspicuous)............. 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,439]" box="[151,1437,241,263]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
<keyLead box="[151,1437,241,263]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
- Pronotum rust brown to reddish; elytra with basal two-thirds darker than apical onethird................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Busanello &amp; Irmler &amp; Caron" authorityYear="2020" box="[1299,1437,242,263]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudastenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis box="[1299,1314,242,263]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1326,1437,242,263]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">ferrugineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="142">6. Larger, at least 3.00 mm long; elytra bicolored, dark brown to black in anterior half and light brown in posterior half; aedeagus with apical sclerites of internal sac not elongate............................................................. 7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
- Smaller, 
<quantity box="[312,397,330,351]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.20 mm</quantity>
long; elytra unicolored light brown; aedeagus with apical sclerites of internal sac elongate and straight............................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Busanello &amp; Irmler &amp; Caron" authorityYear="2020" box="[1299,1436,359,380]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudastenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonicus">
<emphasis box="[1299,1436,359,380]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">P. amazonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,439]" box="[151,1437,388,410]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
<keyLead box="[151,1437,388,410]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
7. Head light brown; median lobe of aedeagus with apical sclerites entirely narrow and S-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1142,1258,388,410]" captionStart="FIGURES 46–47" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1161,1186]" captionTargetBox="[247,1380,261,1071]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,181,1135]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 46–47. Aedeagus of Pseudastenus plaumanni. 46. Dissected from the lectotype (FMNH), dorsal view. 47. Dissected from a specimen collected in the type locality, dorsal and lateral view, respectively. Details: a, basal sclerite; b, apical sclerite; c, basal sclerite of the ejaculatory duct; d, apical sclerite of the ejaculatory duct. Scale bars: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3724305" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3724305/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">Figs. 46–47</figureCitation>
).... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bierig" authorityYear="1939" box="[1310,1437,388,410]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xenaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plaumanni">
<emphasis box="[1310,1437,388,410]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">P. plaumanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,439]" box="[151,1437,417,439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
<keyLead box="[151,1437,417,439]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
- Head dark brown; median lobe of aedeagus with apical sclerites broad on the basal half and not S-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1249,1319,417,439]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–54" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1895,1920]" captionTargetBox="[232,1346,220,1805]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[164,1424,181,1869]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 48–54. Aedeagus of Pseudastenus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively, figures 51–54 including microscopic detail of basal slerites. 48. P. ribeirocostae sp. nov.; 49. P. ferrugineus sp. nov.; 50. P. latus sp. nov.; 51. P. barretoi; 52. P. oculatus sp. nov.; 53. P. amazonicus sp. nov.; 54. P. schubarti sp. nov. Scale bar: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3724309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3724309/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
)... 
